<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="217" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,292,568]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,287,292,317]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">Comments.</emphasis>
Identification at species level is not given because most of the records for Central and South America have been determined as 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1775" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" box="[434,830,327,352]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Grylllus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="assimilis">
<emphasis box="[434,630,328,352]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">Grylllus assimilis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Fabricius" box="[644,821,327,352]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" refString="Fabricius, J. C. (1775) Systema entomologiae, sistens insectorum classes, ordines, genera, species, adiectis synonymis, locis, descriptionibus, observationibus, In Officina Libraria Kortii, Flensbvrgi et Lipsiae, 832 pp." type="book" year="1775">Fabricius, 1775</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
when in fact this species probably does not have such a wide distribution. Most of the records were made in base of the original description by 
<bibRefCitation author="Saussure" box="[1139,1313,364,388]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" refString="Saussure, H. (1874) Etudes sur les insectes orthopteres, famille des gryllides. Mission scientifique au Mexique et dans l'Amerique centrale, 6, 296 - 515." type="journal article" year="1874">Saussure (1874</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Saussure" box="[1324,1381,364,388]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" refString="Saussure, H. (1877) Melanges orthopterologiques V. fascicule Gryllides. Memoires de la Societe de Physique et d'Histoire Naturelle de Geneve, 25 (1), 169 - 504." type="journal article" year="1877">1877</bibRefCitation>
) and they can actually be little studied species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,292,568]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">
A revision of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[482,566,436,460]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Gryllus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[482,566,436,460]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">Gryllus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is badly needed. Significant contributions have been made by 
<bibRefCitation pageId="16" pageNumber="217" refString="David, J. A. O., Zefa, E. &amp; Fontanetti, C. S. (2003) Cryptic species of Gryllus in the light of bioacoustic (Orthoptera: Gryllidae). Neotropical Entomology, 32 (1), 75 - 80. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1590 / S 1519 - 566 X 2003000100010" type="journal article">
David 
<emphasis box="[1377,1436,436,460]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">et al.</emphasis>
(2003)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Desutter-Grandcolas" box="[241,699,471,496]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" refString="Desutter-Grandcolas, L. &amp; Robillard, T. (2003) Phylogeny and the evolution of calling songs in Gryllus (Insecta, Orthoptera, Gryllidae). Zoologica Scripta, 32 (2), 173 - 183. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1046 / j. 1463 - 6409.2003.00107. x" type="journal article" year="2003">Desutter-Grandcolas &amp; Robillard (2003)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Martins" box="[756,1017,471,496]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" refString="Martins, L. P. &amp; Zefa, E. (2011) Contribution to the taxonomy of Gryllus Linnaeus, 1758 in South America: Part I: Redescription of Gryllus argentinus Saussure, 1874 (Orthoptera, Grylloidea, Gryllidae). Entomological Science, 14 (1), 87 - 93. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1479 - 8298.2010.00412. x" type="journal article" year="2011">Martins &amp; Zefa (2011)</bibRefCitation>
. Provisionally, we provide figures of the specimen, which could belong to any of the species described for the region.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,292,568]" box="[199,836,543,568]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,454,543,568]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">Specimens examined.</emphasis>
1 male (
<figureCitation box="[552,643,543,568]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1601,1623]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,617,1569]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[150,1436,613,1579]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 22. Gryllidae: Gryllinae, Gryllus sp. Male. Rostrum (A), tegmina (B), genitalia (C) and lateral habitus (D). Scale bar 0.1 cm for C and 1 cm for D." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258173/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">Figs. 22</figureCitation>
A–D) (PSO-CZ).
</paragraph>
